AGI - Greenland launches the challenge to Donald Trump: "We are not on sale and we cannot simply be taken. Our future is decided by us in Greenland. We don't want to be American or Danish. We're Greenland. Americans and their leaders must understand this," wrote Premier Mute Egede in a Facebook post, six days before the Greenland legislative elections.&nbsp;
Egede's response comes a few hours from the intervention of the American president who, in front of Congress, reiterated the desire to annex the &nbsp; Groenlandia&nbsp; "in one way or another". Trump called the autonomous Danish island a "strongly important land from the military standpoint for our security. We will look forward to your self-determination - it was the message that tycoon addressed to the Greenlanders - but at the same time "we will welcome you to open arms in the United States if you choose it". &nbsp;
Words that have also caused the reaction of Denmark: "Trump wants to take Greenland? It will not happen," said Danish Defence Minister Trouls Lund Poulsen to public broadcaster DR. "The direction Greenland wants to take will be decided by the Greenlanders."
